@startuml HealSense_Data_Flow
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Dynamic.puml
LAYOUT_TOP_DOWN()
title HealSense: Complete End-to-End Data Flow

Person(patient, "Patient")
System(iot, "IoT Sensor Unit\n(ESP32/Arduino)")
System(mobile, "Mobile App\n(Flutter)")
System(api_gw, "API Gateway\n(FastAPI)")
System(vital_svc, "Vital Signs Service")
System(ml_svc, "ML Inference Service")
System(alert_svc, "Alert Service")
System(db, "PostgreSQL Database")
System(redis, "Redis Cache")
System(realtime, "WebSocket Manager")
System(notify, "Notification Service")
System(web_dash, "Web Dashboard\n(React)")
Person(provider, "Healthcare Provider")

note as scenario_1
SCENARIO 1: Vital Sign Collection
Vital sign measurement and storage
end note

Rel(patient, iot, "1. Wears/activates", "Physical")
Rel(iot, api_gw, "2. Transmits vital data\n{HR: 78, SpO2: 98.5, Temp: 37.1, BP: 120/78}", "REST/MQTT")
Rel(api_gw, vital_svc, "3. Validate vital signs", "Internal Call")
Rel(vital_svc, db, "4. Store vital record", "INSERT vital_signs table")
Rel(db, redis, "5. Cache latest vital (TTL: 5min)", "SET cache")
Rel(vital_svc, ml_svc, "6. Send for risk prediction", "Internal Call")

note as scenario_2
SCENARIO 2: ML-Based Risk Prediction
Machine learning inference and classification
end note

Rel(ml_svc, ml_svc, "7. Normalize features\nusing StandardScaler", "Feature Engineering")
Rel(ml_svc, ml_svc, "8. Run LSTM inference\n(60-timestep sequence)", "TensorFlow")
Rel(ml_svc, ml_svc, "9. Return health status\n{status: NORMAL, risk_score: 0.15}", "Prediction")
Rel(ml_svc, vital_svc, "10. Return classification", "Response")

note as scenario_3
SCENARIO 3: Alert Generation
Alert creation based on predictions and thresholds
end note

Rel(vital_svc, alert_svc, "11. Check alert conditions\nif (status != NORMAL)", "Conditional Logic")
Rel(alert_svc, db, "12. Create alert record\nif threshold exceeded", "INSERT alerts table")
Rel(alert_svc, realtime, "13. Broadcast alert event", "WebSocket Pub/Sub")

note as scenario_4
SCENARIO 4: Real-Time Notification
Multi-channel alert delivery to stakeholders
end note

Rel(realtime, notify, "14. Dispatch notifications", "Internal")
Rel(notify, mobile, "15a. Push notification", "Firebase FCM")
Rel(notify, web_dash, "15b. WebSocket alert", "Real-time Stream")
Rel(notify, notify, "15c. Email/SMS delivery", "External Services")
Rel(mobile, patient, "16a. Alert on phone screen", "UI Display")
Rel(web_dash, provider, "16b. Alert in dashboard", "UI Display")

note as scenario_5
SCENARIO 5: Provider Dashboard Update
Provider monitoring and intervention
end note

Rel(provider, web_dash, "17. Views patient data", "Browser Action")
Rel(web_dash, api_gw, "18. Request patient profile", "GET /patients/{id}")
Rel(api_gw, vital_svc, "19. Fetch latest vitals", "Query")
Rel(vital_svc, redis, "20. Check cache (hit)", "GET cache")
Rel(redis, api_gw, "21. Return cached data", "Cached Response")
Rel(api_gw, web_dash, "22. Display vitals + trends", "JSON Response")
Rel(provider, api_gw, "23. Acknowledge alert", "POST /alerts/{id}/acknowledge")
Rel(api_gw, alert_svc, "24. Mark acknowledged", "Update Status")
Rel(alert_svc, realtime, "25. Broadcast acknowledgment", "Event")
Rel(realtime, mobile, "26. Update mobile UI", "Real-time Update")

note as note_database
DATABASE TABLES INVOLVED:
- vital_signs: Raw measurements
- alerts: Alert records
- patients: Patient info
- devices: Device tracking
- users: Provider accounts
end note

note as note_flow
DATA FLOW CHARACTERISTICS:
- Latency: <500ms end-to-end
- Frequency: Every 30-60 seconds
- Throughput: Multiple concurrent patients
- Reliability: At-least-once delivery
- History: 30-day retention
end note

@enduml
